Frank Hall Crane https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Hall_Crane 0 Frank Hall Crane (January 1, 1873 – September 1, 1948) was an American stage and film actor and director. He appeared in 75 films between 1909 and 1939. He also directed 48 films between 1914 and 1927. His first screen writing included The Stolen Voice in 1915. He was born in San Francisco, California, and died in Woodland Hills, Los Angeles. Frank_Hall_Crane ( January_1 , 1873 – September_1_,_1948 ) was an_American_stage_and_film_actor_and_director .
